<div class="page-header" style="border:none">
  <h1>Do I qualify for Early Head Start?</h1>

<div class="lead">
  <p>Early Head Start provides educational and early childhood development activities for children from birth to three years old from low-income families. It includes free medical, dental, and mental health services and nutritious meals, as well as parent education and training.</p>
  </div>

  <p>You can find more information on Early Head Start <a href="http://chicagoearlylearning.org/faq">here</a></p>
</div>


      <% if @eligible %>

      <div class="panel panel-default" style="margin: 0 0 40px 0">
        <div class="panel-body">
          <p style="font-size:32px; font-style:italic">You may be in luck!</p>
        <p>Based on the ages of your children, household size, and income, you likely qualify for Early Head Start. <p> For application information please visit chicagoearlylearning.org to find early learning programs near you or call the Chicago: Ready to Learn! Hotline at (312) 229-1690.</p>
      </div>

      <% else %>

<div class="panel panel-default" style="margin: 0 0 40px 0">
        <div class="panel-body">
          <p style="font-size:32px; font-style:italic">We apologize.</p>
        <p>Based on the age of your children, household size and income, you likely do not qualify for Early Head Start.</p>
        <p> If you need assistance, please call the Illinois Action for Children at 312.823.1100.</p>
        </div>
      <% end %>
      </div>

